ing of the ecological consequences of environmental changes, especially those that occur simultaneously over large areas, will require information about the spatial scaling of their effects on local population dynamics. Journal of Animal Ecology (2007) 76, 315-325 doi: 10.1111/j.1365-2656.2006.01195.x},
