is is probably due to the strong impact of the reproductive effort theory (Williams 1966, Schaffer 1974, Charlesworth 1980) which analyses the demographic consequences of allocation of already acquired resources to somatic versus reproductive func-tions, without consideration of acquisition aspects. The need for an integration of the theories of optimal foraging and life history evolution was indicated},
