sitive vital rate differed by management scenario and confidence was higher for larger populations. Results for both species might change given other conditions and/or age structures. The VRSA should be an effective tool for wildlife managers who want to compare alternative management strategies to increase population size. A downloadable Excel spread sheet for calculating VRSA for a life-table is available at http://ase.tufts.edu/biology/faculty/reed/software.html.},
